**EDITING SETTINGS.XML FILE:**

1. Go to path &quot;D:\apache-maven-3.3.9-bin\apache-maven-3.3.9\conf&quot;
2. Open settings.xml file and edit the &lt;proxies&gt; tag as:

&lt;proxies&gt;

      &lt;proxy&gt;

      &lt;id&gt;optional&lt;/id&gt;

     &lt;active&gt;true&lt;/active&gt;

      &lt;protocol&gt;http&lt;/protocol&gt;

      &lt;username&gt;cts\Your EmpID&lt;/username&gt;

      &lt;password&gt;Provide your password&lt;/password&gt;

      &lt;host&gt;proxy.cognizant.com&lt;/host&gt;

      &lt;port&gt;6050&lt;/port&gt;

 &lt;/proxy&gt;

 &lt;/proxies&gt;

**DOWNLOAD AND INSTALL GIT:**

1. Download GIT by clicking on the link [https://git-for-windows.github.io/](https://git-for-windows.github.io/)
2. Double click on the file downloaded and select &quot;Run&quot;.
3. Complete the install wizard.
4. Check if GITis properly installed in your system using command &quot;git --version&quot; in command prompt.

**DOWNLOAD AND INSTALL ECLIPSE IDE:**

1. Raise a phoenix request for eclipse software &quot;Eclipse Mars&quot;.
2. To raise phoenix request follow the steps given below:
  1. Click on the link [https://onecognizant.cognizant.com/](https://onecognizant.cognizant.com/).
  2. In the app store search for phoenix.
  3. Give install Eclipse Mars as problem statement.
  4. Raise a request.
  5. If you have further doubts do chat with &quot;experttouch&quot;.
3. Once the software is installed open the folder and double click on the .exe file to open and work with eclipse.
4. Install Maven plugin from store by following the steps given below:
  1. Go to Help -&gt; Eclipse Marketplace
  2. Search by Maven
  3. Click &quot;Install&quot; button at &quot;Maven Integration for Eclipse&quot; section
  4. Follow the instruction step by step till finish.

1. Install egit plugin from store by following the steps given below:
  1. Go to Help -&gt; Install New Software
  2. Copy URL [http://download.eclipse.org/egit/updates/](http://download.eclipse.org/egit/updates/) and click enter.
  3. When the site loads, select the features to install, or click the  **Select All**  button.
  4. To properly resolve all dependencies, check
    1. [x] Contact all update sites during install to find required software
  5. Click Next, agree to the license terms, and install.

**OTHER SOFTWARE REQUIRED:**
